Activity: A8 - Discover cryptography used in Internet of Things devices

Objective
The goal of this activity was to investigate and identify cryptographic methods used in LoT devices to secure data, authenticate users, and prevent unauthorised access

Method
I examined the security settings of several IoT devices I own, including a smart thermostat, a smart door lock, and a smart speaker. I looked at how they protect

Findings
The IoT devices I analysed use the following cryptographic implementations:
1. Wifi encryption - all the devices connect to the home network using WPA2 and WPA3 encryption, ensuring data transmitted overWiFi is secure
2. Secure passwor storage - device apps require strong passwords which are stored in a hashed format using modern algorithms
3. Two-factor authentication - some devices' companion apps support two factor authentication for an extra layer of authentication

Security Principle
These cryptographic implementations support confidentiality, integrity, and authentication. they prevent unauthorised access, ensure transmitted data isn't tampered with, and verify the identity of users and devices.

